OL,3,GOPINIONCTerrestrial TV switch-off: a
OL,4,Cheadline the government can't afford
OL,5,
OL,6,FYou may have noticed that things have
OL,7,Fnot been going too well for the
OL,8,Fgovernment of late.
OL,10,FSome Labour supporters would blame a
OL,11,Fnumber of own goals ` beginning with
OL,12,Fthe decision to scrap universal winter
OL,13,Ffuel payments ` for their unpopularity.
OL,15,FSo the last thing the government needs
OL,16,Fis another own goal.
OL,18,FIt is vitally important that decisions
OL,19,Fin support of broadcasters' move
OL,20,Ftowards internet delivery are not
OL,21,Fconflated with turning off terrestrial
OL,22,Ftelevision.
OL,23,EPub: 14-Jun-2026Upppppppppppppppppppppp
OL,24,ANext PageBClean FeedCNat TVFOn This Day
FL,147,140,200,120,0,100
PN,14602
SC,0002
CT,3,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F146A1782648717
OL,1,W~+$ hw1~{4~k4 ~shw1~sj7}         G2/8
OL,2,W+.!+,"-$/*%/*% / "-$+,*-'U(,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,3,GOPINIONCTerrestrial TV switch-off: a
OL,4,Cheadline the government can't afford
OL,5,
OL,6,FInternet delivery offers opportunities
OL,7,F` UHD pictures and more seamless
OL,8,Fconnections between linear and on
OL,9,Fdemand services.
OL,11,FYes, turning off terrestrial TV can
OL,12,Falso cut distribution costs.
OL,14,FBut it is surely blindingly obvious
OL,15,Fthat there can be no question of
OL,16,Fturning off terrestrial TV until very
OL,17,Ffew people rely on it.
OL,23,EPub: 14-Jun-2026Upppppppppppppppppppppp
OL,24,ANext PageBClean FeedCNat TVFOn This Day
FL,147,140,200,120,0,100
PN,14603
SC,0003
CT,3,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F146A1782648717
OL,1,W~+$ hw1~{4~k4 ~shw1~sj7}         G3/8
OL,2,W+.!+,"-$/*%/*% / "-$+,*-'U(,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,3,GOPINIONCTerrestrial TV switch-off: a
OL,4,Cheadline the government can't afford
OL,5,
OL,6,FEven setting a 2034 date just now risks
OL,7,Fcausing fear and anxiety amongst the
OL,8,Felderly and vulnerable. Not to mention
OL,9,Fnegative stories that people will be
OL,10,F"forced" to buy new equipment or be
OL,11,Fforced to get broadband.
OL,13,FIf broadcasters want to switch off
OL,14,Fterrestrial, they will need to convince
OL,15,Fmost of us that watching TV over the
OL,16,Finternet offers a better experience.
OL,18,FJust as Freeview offered widescreen,
OL,19,Fmore channels and, later, HD so
OL,20,Fbroadcasters need to start telling us
OL,21,Fjust why Freely is a positive choice.
OL,23,EPub: 14-Jun-2026Upppppppppppppppppppppp
OL,24,ANext PageBClean FeedCNat TVFOn This Day
FL,147,140,200,120,0,100
PN,14604
SC,0004
CT,3,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F146A1782648717
OL,1,W~+$ hw1~{4~k4 ~shw1~sj7}         G4/8
OL,2,W+.!+,"-$/*%/*% / "-$+,*-'U(,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,3,GOPINIONCTerrestrial TV switch-off: a
OL,4,Cheadline the government can't afford
OL,5,
OL,6,FThere also needs to be an easy way to
OL,7,Fupgrade all existing sets ` just as
OL,8,Fvirtually any UHF set, however old,
OL,9,Fcould be adapted for Freeview.
OL,11,FHowever it should also be remembered
OL,12,Fthat there appears to be a portion of
OL,13,Fthe population ` many of whom are
OL,14,Flikely to be elderly or vulnerable `
OL,15,Fwho simply do not want broadband for
OL,16,Fwhatever reason.
OL,18,FA suggested way forward from
OL,19,Ftransmitter operator Arqiva would seem
OL,20,Fvery sensible.
OL,23,EPub: 14-Jun-2026Upppppppppppppppppppppp
OL,24,ANext PageBClean FeedCNat TVFOn This Day
FL,147,140,200,120,0,100
